1. this serie of anglo-saxon work will be
             printed in a handsome style, on a fin paper, in large octavo.
2. it is expected that the volume will extende to about thirty sheets: and
             the price to subscribe for a volume of that
             size is fixed at 25s.; to non-subscribe the
             price will be 31s. 6d.
3. the first volume will be put to press as soon as eighty
             subscribes’ name are received, and the subscription will close
             for each work upon its publication; and it will be optional to any
             subscriber to discontinue his name from any
             portion of the series.
4. the subscribers’ name will be printed with each author, and
             gentleman are particularly rekuested to write the style in which they
             desire their name to appear.
5. each volume will occupy six month in the
             printing; and no delay shall take place in proceeding with as much
             expedition as is consistent with accuracy, till the completion of
             the whole series.
